messages.content: What is the latest version of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?
The latest version of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils is 0.4.3.
What bug was fixed in version 0.4.3 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?
In version 0.4.3 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the bug that caused the ExecutionTime Node to not work with the latest version of ComfyUI was fixed.
What enhancement was made to the ExecutionTime Node in version 0.4.2?
In version 0.4.2 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the enhancement was made to ignore the ExecutionTime Node when saving the API.
Does ComfyUI-Dev-Utils support comfy-cli?
Yes, ComfyUI-Dev-Utils started supporting Comfy-Org/comfy-cli from version 0.4.1.
What was the enhancement made in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils version 0.4.0?
In version 0.4.0 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the enhancement made was to save the LogConsole panel 'Collapsed' state.
What bug was fixed in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils version 0.4.0?
In version 0.4.0 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the bug fix was to remove the 'prompt_id' judgment from ExecutionTime to make it compatible with ComfyUI-Workflow-Component.
What new feature was added in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils version 0.3.0?
In version 0.3.0 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the new feature added was the Log Console.
What new feature was introduced in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils version 0.2.0?
In version 0.2.0 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the new feature introduced was the support for exporting Execution Time CSV files.
What enhancements were made to the Execution Time Node in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils version 0.2.0?
In version 0.2.0 of ComfyUI-Dev-Utils, the enhancements made to the Execution Time Node were optimizing its style to make it better resize and supporting auto-resize.
What is ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?
ComfyUI-Dev-Utils is a set of custom nodes and utilities for ComfyUI that provide additional features and enhancements for development and debugging.
How can you install ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?
ComfyUI-Dev-Utils can be installed either through ComfyUI-Manager or manually by cloning the GitHub repository into the custom_nodes directory of ComfyUI and installing the required dependencies.
What is the Execution Time Analysis Tool in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?

The Execution Time Analysis Tool in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils adds a Badge to the upper left corner of a node to display its execution time, an Execution Time node to display execution times in a table, and a Clear Execution Cache button to unload models and free memory.
What is the Log Console feature in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?

The Log Console in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils provides a Console panel that displays Python logs, capturing output from print, logging, stdout, and stderr. It is based on SSE, supports text color, lazy startup, and can be completely disabled.
How does ComfyUI-Dev-Utils enhance the Reroute functionality?
ComfyUI-Dev-Utils adds a Reroute option to the node slot menu and optimizes the deletion of Reroute Nodes, making it easier to manage and remove reroutes in ComfyUI.
What does the UrlDownload node in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils do?
The UrlDownload node in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils allows downloading files from remote URLs and provides the file path.
What is the purpose of the UploadAnything node in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils?
The UploadAnything node in ComfyUI-Dev-Utils enables uploading any file and provides the file path.
Under what license is ComfyUI-Dev-Utils available?
ComfyUI-Dev-Utils is available under the MIT license.
